<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4419] leveled compaction generates too small sstables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4419</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I set sstable_size_in_mb to 96 I end up with sstable data files no larger than 60M.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This in turn messes up the LeveledManifest calculation since it finds compaction candidates by summing up the size of sstables at a particular level and comparing it to the configured size multiplied by the desired number of sstables at a level, resulting in ~20 sstables in level 1 instead of the 10 that one would expect from looking at LeveledManifest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some additional logging here reveals that the position parameter passed to LeveledCompactionTask.newSSTableSegmentThresholdReached() is significantly higher than the size of the output file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
