                            <comment id="13407993" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 6 Jul 2012 13:41:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is that compaction is considering uncompressed size for position (and thus cut segments at 96MB of uncompressed data) while the manifest consider compressed sizes for level sizes. This was fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4341&quot; title=&quot;Small SSTable Segments Can Hurt Leveling Process&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4341&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4341&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for cassandra-1.1, but I guess we might want to backport that part of the patch to 1.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13411329" author="slebresne" created="Wed, 11 Jul 2012 08:48:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that extract the relevant part from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4341&quot; title=&quot;Small SSTable Segments Can Hurt Leveling Process&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-4341&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-4341&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
